Common.Highlight.Common.Text: NLA of 29sqm* plus one car space
Adjacent to the future Crows Nest Metro

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
CBRE, as the exclusive sales agent, is pleased to present to you Suite 203, 6-8 Clarke Street, Crows Nest. 

6-8 Clarke Street, Crows Nest is a three-storey office building consisting of a total of 26 strata suites. The subject property at Suite 203, located on the second floor of the building, has an NLA of 29sqm* and a single car space. 

6-8 Clarke Street holds substantial development potential beyond its current improvements. In the case of a collective sale between the remaining strata owners of the building, the property could capitalise on future increased planning controls (STCA). 

Commanding a premium location just metres from the future Metro and in immediate vicinity of Crows Nests main retail and dining strip along Willoughby Road, the property’s full development potential and capital growth is yet to be realised.

6-8 Clarke Street, Crows Nest benefits from the following key attributes: 

- Net lettable area of 29sqm* plus one car space
- Adjacent to the future Crows Nest Metro Station Development
- Net passing income of $11,770 per annum*
- Located within the rapidly growing St Leonards/Crows Nest priority precinct
- Significant development potential offered in the case of a collective strata sale (STCA)
- Ideal for owner occupiers, investors and land bankers

Suite 203, 6-8 Clarke Street is being sold via public auction on Tuesday, 17th December 2019 at 10.30am

For further details, please contact the exclusive sales agents.

 Nest.

Common.Strapline.Common.Text: WHOLE UNIT BLOCK IN CROWS NEST

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
CBRE, as the exclusive selling agent, is please to present 56 Falcon Street, Crows Nest. The property is a secure apartment block investment located just metres from the Crows Nest dining and commercial core. With both St Leonards Station and the future Crows Nest Metro located within 1km* of the property, 56 Falcon Street capitalises greatly from its connectivity to the North Shore and Sydney CBD and potential for future growth.

56 Falcon Street benefits from the following key attributes:

- Currently comprises four large two bedroom apartments each equipped with 1 bathroom, laundry and study
- Gross income of $130,618 per annum* with opportunity to increase to market rent
- Estimated market gross income of $162,686 p.a.*
- 512sqm* land area with 4 car spaces
- R3 Medium Density Residential zoning with 8.5m height limit
- Located just moments to Crows Nest dining and commercial core
- Strong growth suburb in high demand

*approximate

CBRE, as the exclusive sales agent, is pleased to present 39-47 Albany Street, Crows Nest. Located just metres from Crows Nest Village and a short walk to St Leonards Station and the future Metro, this three-storey freehold building offers over 3,200sqm of quality office space in one of the most rapidly growing commercial precincts in NSW. Well-positioned to capitalise on the transforming St Leonard/Crows Nest priority precinct, the property also affords significant rental reversion opportunities as well as potential development upside in the future (STCA)

39-47 Albany Street benefits from the following key attributes:

- Net income of $1,174,844 per annum*
- NLA of 3,287sqm* plus 43 car spaces
- Massive 1,609sqm* land area – one of the largest remaining land holdings in Crows Nest
- 100% leased with WALE (income) of over 3 years*
- Three-storey freehold office building with large floor plates over 1,000sqm
- Significant value-add opportunities through rental reversion or future development (STCA)
- Set to benefit from the rapid growth of the St Leonards/Crows Nest priority precinct
- Short walk to Crows Nest Village, St Leonards Station and future Crows Nest Metro Station
- 4-Star NABERS Energy rating

Interested parties are invited to submit their expressions of interest for the purchase of 39-47 Albany Street,
Crows Nest by Wednesday, 12 August 2020 at 4pm.

*Approximate

Note: All financial figures have been provided by the Vendor. Purchasers are advised to conduct their own independent due diligence.
